The paper deals with the problem of Visual Question Answering, which requires a combination of concepts from Computer Vision and Natural Language Processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel graph-based approach that combines a graph learner module with graph convolutions, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and deep learning. This suggests that the paper could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
